{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y2tDT4vLeHzE8wn3uDXcSy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the problem. The ConfigMap for Elasticsearch is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting. For a new Elasticsearch 7.x cluster (which has no existing data/cluster state), the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` bootstrap setting is required for initial cluster formation. Without it, nodes can't elect a master and log \"master not discovered yet\".\n\nThe current `elasticsearch.yml` has:\n- `cluster.name: es-cluster`\n- `node.name: ${POD_NAME}`\n- `node.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]`\n- `network.host: 0.0.0.0`\n- `discovery.seed_hosts` for node discovery\n- `node.store.allow_mmap: false`\n\nBut it's missing the critical `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting needed to bootstrap a fresh 7.x cluster. The solution is to add this setting with all three node names to the ConfigMap, restart the pods to apply the change, and then remove it once the cluster successfully forms since it's only needed for initial bootstrap. With the Parallel pod management policy, I can delete all the pods at once and let the StatefulSet recreate them simultaneously. Now I need to check whether the PVCs already exist and if there's any persisted data I should be aware of.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1536,"cache_read_input_tokens":31738,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1536},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78a5a234-ddf9-40cc-9d21-db130fa6e89d","uuid":"489df6d7-a49e-488a-9f03-930f40c4fcec","request_id":"req_011CccEyp6cCo1bbaCJ7EXQM"}
