{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GhufbRcJTEjhNLM4ZHuU6w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only a `node.lock` file exists under `nodes/0/`, with no actual cluster state (no `_state` directory). This means the cluster has never formed a master and hasn't bootstrapped. The `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting is needed.\n\nThe fix:\n1. Update the ConfigMap to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [\"es-cluster-0\", \"es-cluster-1\", \"es-cluster-2\"]`\n2. Restart the pods (delete them - StatefulSet will recreate them) so they pick up the new config\n3. Let the cluster form and elect a master\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap afterward—it's a bootstrap-only setting that should be stripped out once the cluster has state to avoid accidental re-bootstrapping on future restarts\n5. Do a rolling restart to confirm stability\n\nThe plan is to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap, restart the pods to pick up the change, wait for the cluster to be healthy, then remove that setting and do another rolling restart. Since the StatefulSet has parallel pod management, deleting pods will recreate them simultaneously, which is fine for bootstrapping. The constraint about not recreating the cluster is satisfied because restarting pods isn't the same as recreating the cluster itself. The ConfigMap is mounted as a subPath volume, so pods need to restart to see the updated configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":283,"cache_read_input_tokens":34405,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":283},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78a5a234-ddf9-40cc-9d21-db130fa6e89d","uuid":"bcfbc513-ae8d-4c3f-b6d1-8e2a