{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FyfERAL5LHTpsjCs11RbV4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals met:\n\n**Root cause:** The ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which ES 7.x requires for a brand-new cluster to bootstrap quorum and elect a master. Without it, all nodes log \"master not discovered yet\" indefinitely.\n\n**What was done:**\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** to the ConfigMap, listing all 3 pods — this is the one-time bootstrap signal that lets nodes elect an initial master.\n2. **Restarted all pods simultaneously** (subPath mounts don't hot-reload, and initial bootstrap requires all nodes to start together for quorum).\n3. **Cluster formed** — status green, 3 nodes, master elected on `es-cluster-1`.\n4. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** from the ConfigMap — this bootstrap-only setting must not persist because if left in place it can cause a cluster split if nodes disagree on it during a future restart.\n5. **Rolling restart** — restarted each pod in turn while verifying cluster stayed green with 3 nodes after each one. Master re-elected to `es-cluster-0` without disruption.\n\n**Final state:** cluster `green`, 3/3 nodes, master elected (`es-cluster-0`), 6 active shards, ConfigMap contains only runtime-safe settings."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":667,"cache_read_input_tokens":38642,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":667},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78a5a234-ddf9-40cc-9d21-db130fa6e89d","uuid":"2d20d3bd-b9d3-46c2-b788-5a88483e231f","request_id":"req_011CccFZjUFNahevUBqXvzTj"}
